---
title: Mexican-Inspired Calabacitas Con Queso Zucchini with Tortillas & Cilantro
description: Inspired by members of the HelloFresh community, we share this delicious 30-minute vegetarian dinner idea in honor of Hispanic Heritage Month. “Preparing a meal is our way of showing we love each other,” says Ashley H., whose family is from Mexico. “My grandmother always says, ‘Primero comemos,” or “First, we eat.” For this homestyle dish, you’ll toss sautéed zucchini, corn, tomato, and onion in a creamy sauce, then top with melted cheddar and sprinkle with fresh cilantro. Our spin on calabacitas con queso is served with warm tortillas for scooping up all that savory, melty goodness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64dbd19f7e32e9eeac712a85-6a63f963.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64dbd19f7e32e9eeac712a85.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 840 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mexican-inspired-calabacitas-con-queso-64dbd19f7e32e9eeac712a85
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce. Drain @corn{1%unit}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, core, and dice @long green pepper{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and halve @zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over high heat. Add corn and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred in spots, ~{2-4%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium.

Add onion, green pepper, zucchini, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, and a large drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add tomato and @water{½%cup}; cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and sauce has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> For 4 servings, you may want to work in batches.

Stir @sour cream{4.5%tablespoon} into veggies until combined, then sprinkle evenly with @cheddar cheese{½%cup}. Cover and cook until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Toast your tortillas on the stove if you prefer a crispier texture.

Divide calabacitas con queso between #bowls{} and garnish with cilantro.

> TIP: For a little heat, drizzle with hot sauce from your pantry!

Serve with tortillas on the side.